    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderManXPU_Bike.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderManXPU_Bike.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089556702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/623509593/RenderManXPU_Bike.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089556702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"844\" data-width=\"1500\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623640612\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManXPU_Bike.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"623509593\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"7\" data-media-id=\"5bcef00b-999d-40cc-8a2f-e7c4adc9c042\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderManXPU_Bike.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089556702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1500&amp;height=844 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderManXPU_Bike.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089556702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427 1x\"></span><p>Two essential and commonly used geometry patterns in procedural shading are Ambient Occlusion and Curvature.  RenderMan can render both of these features, which can be used either in a procedural shading network or baked out and re-read by a PxrTexture node.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><a href=\"/wiki/download/attachments/623509593/RenderManFundaMentals_MidnightRebel_Teaser.mp4?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760091039954&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760\">RenderManFundaMentals_MidnightRebel_Teaser.mp4</a></span><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"02b3d48b-b651-4c91-935a-13fea6639e2a\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">PxrDirt (Ambient Occlusion)</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>The <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://rmanwiki-27.pixar.com/space/REN27/542223198\" rel=\"nofollow\">PxrDirt</a> node renders local geometric occlusion. </p><p>This is useful for applying shading effects, such as dirt, rust, and dust, into the nooks and crevices of your model.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Dirt_1.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderMan_Dirt_1.jpg?version=2&amp;modificationDate=1760089463390&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/623509593/RenderMan_Dirt_1.jpg?version=2&amp;modificationDate=1760089463390&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1080\" data-width=\"1920\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623607851\" data-linked-resource-version=\"2\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Dirt_1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"623509593\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"7\" data-media-id=\"93b67797-6316-479c-85f0-1bbbafa8defb\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderMan_Dirt_1.jpg?version=2&amp;modificationDate=1760089463390&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=854 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderMan_Dirt_1.jpg?version=2&amp;modificationDate=1760089463390&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427 1x\"></span><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"fd8a08b0-d175-43f0-87f2-a9b4e90d544f\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">PxrCurvature</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>The <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://rmanwiki-27.pixar.com/space/REN27/542223097\" rel=\"nofollow\">PxrCurvature</a> node is a practical, straightforward way to create edge effects and curvature-based results, such as edge wear, edge breakup, and edge variation on plastics and objects in contact with other surfaces.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Curvature.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderMan_Curvature.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089400057&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/623509593/RenderMan_Curvature.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089400057&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1080\" data-width=\"1920\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623542387\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Curvature.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"623509593\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"7\" data-media-id=\"1eaca92e-3963-4e58-9b9a-06a2da931c4a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderMan_Curvature.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089400057&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=854 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/RenderMan_Curvature.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760089400057&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427 1x\"></span><p>One practical example of these two nodes is using a PxrCurvature node as a layer mask between two layers, such as a base metal and a paint layer on top, as seen in the Midnight Rebel scene.  </p><p>The PxrDirt node can then be used as a layer mask to add dust to the paint layer.</p><p>The video Material Layering lesson below dives into these nodes in more detail</p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"bc1ed3e1-9f3f-409b-be22-209766d44434\" data-macro-id=\"f445dd7e084ec4ed2bca3617595ff1c19d3b83fb78174651a8f2d5bd83a3628e\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521400282\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p /><p>The model and scene can be downloaded here for you to follow along and practice with.</p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://assets.renderman.pixar.com/Tutorials/renderman-fundamentals/render_man_fundamentals_midnight_rebel.zip\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"DownloadButton2.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760091212379&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=47\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/623509593/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760091212379&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"68\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623509621\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"DownloadButton2.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"623509593\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"7\" data-media-id=\"fd5a3869-2cfb-482f-bc70-b1b7a53f4fec\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760091212379&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=68 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/623509593/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760091212379&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=47 1x\"></span></a>"
    }
  },
